        <body>
      
		<pb n="1"/>
			<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Cincinnati Ohio</placeName></p>
			<p rend="align(right)"><date>19<hi rend="sup">th</hi> January 5609&#47;<lb/>1849</date></p>
			<p>Revd Sir</p>
          <p rend="indent(2)">It is with no small satisfaction I give<lb/> my son <persName>Frederick</persName> this letter of introduction as a<lb/> means for his becoming personally acquainted<lb/> with a gentleman for whom&#44; through his writings&#44; he<lb/> is already impressed with sentiments of esteem and<lb/> respect. He <sic>purposes</sic> passing a week at<lb/> <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>&#44; for any attentions he may experience<lb/> from you I beg to say I shall consider myself your<lb/> debtor.</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">I have requested him to ascertain your senti&#61;<lb/>&#61;ments on my Letters and whether and when it will<lb/> find a place in the occident&#8212;</p>
          <p rend="indent(4)">I remain</p>
          <p rend="indent(5)">Revd Sir yrs. most respectfully</p>
          <p rend="indent(7)"><persName role="author">A A. Lindo</persName></p>
			<p><addressee>Revd. I Leeser</addressee></p>
		<pb n="2"/>
			<p><addressee>Revd. Isc. Leeser</addressee></p>
          <p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
